article.description: — Josh Bannan had 22 points as Montana narrowly defeated Portland State 66-64 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Bannan scores 22 to lift Montana over Portland St. 66-64
article.linkText: Bannan scores 22 to lift Montana over Portland St. 66-64
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Josh Bannan had 22 points as Montana narrowly defeated Portland State 66-64 on Thursday night. Robby Beasley III had 18 points for Montana (12-6, 5-2 Big Sky Conference). Cameron Parker added 13 points. Damion Squire had 17 points for the Vikings (4-10, 2-4). James Jean-Marie added 16 points and nine rebounds. Khalid Thomas had 11 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
